    "description": "DiHydrogen is the second version of the Hydrogen fork of the well-known\ndistributed linear algebra library, Elemental. DiHydrogen aims to be a\nbasic distributed multilinear algebra interface with a particular\nemphasis on the needs of the distributed machine learning effort, LBANN.\n",
    "dependencies": [
        {
            "name": "aluminum",
            "description": "Aluminum provides a generic interface to high-performance communication\nlibraries, with a focus on allreduce algorithms. Blocking and non-\nblocking algorithms and GPU-aware algorithms are supported. Aluminum\nalso contains custom implementations of select algorithms to optimize\nfor certain situations."
        },
        {
            "name": "catch2",
            "description": "Catch2 is a multi-paradigm test framework for C++, which also supports\nObjective-C (and maybe C)."
        },
        {
            "name": "cmake",
            "description": "A cross-platform, open-source build system. CMake is a family of tools\ndesigned to build, test and package software."
        },
        {
            "name": "cuda",
            "description": "CUDA is a parallel computing platform and programming model invented by\nNVIDIA. It enables dramatic increases in computing performance by\nharnessing the power of the graphics processing unit (GPU). Note: This\npackage does not currently install the drivers necessary to run CUDA.\nThese will need to be installed manually. See:\nhttps://docs.nvidia.com/cuda/ for details."
        },
        {
            "name": "cudnn",
            "description": "NVIDIA cuDNN is a GPU-accelerated library of primitives for deep neural\nnetworks"
        },
        {
            "name": "gmake",
            "description": "GNU Make is a tool which controls the generation of executables and\nother non-source files of a program from the program's source files."
        },
        {
            "name": "hip",
            "description": "HIP is a C++ Runtime API and Kernel Language that allows developers to\ncreate portable applications for AMD and NVIDIA GPUs from single source\ncode."
        },
        {
            "name": "hipcub",
            "description": "Radeon Open Compute Parallel Primitives Library"
        },
        {
            "name": "hsa-rocr-dev",
            "description": "This repository includes the user mode API nterfaces and libraries\nnecessary for host applications to launch computer kernels to available\nHSA ROCm kernel agents.AMD Heterogeneous System Architecture HSA - Linux\nHSA Runtime for Boltzmann (ROCm) platforms."
        },
        {
            "name": "hydrogen",
            "description": "Hydrogen: Distributed-memory dense and sparse-direct linear algebra and\noptimization library. Based on the Elemental library."
        },
        {
            "name": "lcov",
            "description": "LCOV is a graphical front-end for GCC's coverage testing tool gcov. It\ncollects gcov data for multiple source files and creates HTML pages\ncontaining the source code annotated with coverage information. It also\nadds overview pages for easy navigation within the file structure. LCOV\nsupports statement, function and branch coverage measurement."
        },
        {
            "name": "llvm-amdgpu",
            "description": "Toolkit for the construction of highly optimized compilers, optimizers,\nand run-time environments."
        },
        {
            "name": "llvm-openmp",
            "description": "The OpenMP subproject of LLVM contains the components required to build\nan executable OpenMP program that are outside the compiler itself."
        },
        {
            "name": "miopen-hip",
            "description": "AMD's library for high performance machine learning primitives."
        },
        {
            "name": "mpi",
            "description": "This is an earlier version of Intel parallel software development tools\nand has now been replaced by the Intel oneAPI Toolkits. LICENSE\nINFORMATION: By downloading and using this software, you agree to the\nterms and conditions of the software license agreements at\nhttps://intel.ly/393CijO."
        },
        {
            "name": "nccl",
            "description": "Optimized primitives for collective multi-GPU communication."
        },
        {
            "name": "ninja",
            "description": "Ninja is a small build system with a focus on speed. It differs from\nother build systems in two major respects: it is designed to have its\ninput files generated by a higher-level build system, and it is designed\nto run builds as fast as possible."
        },
        {
            "name": "nvshmem",
            "description": "NVSHMEM is a parallel programming interface based on OpenSHMEM that\nprovides efficient and scalable communication for NVIDIA GPU clusters.\nNVSHMEM creates a global address space for data that spans the memory of\nmultiple GPUs and can be accessed with fine-grained GPU-initiated\noperations, CPU-initiated operations, and operations on CUDA streams."
        },
        {
            "name": "py-gcovr",
            "description": "Gcovr provides a utility for managing the use of the GNU gcov utility\nand generating summarized code coverage results. This command is\ninspired by the Python coverage.py package, which provides a similar\nutility for Python."
        },
        {
            "name": "roctracer-dev",
            "description": "ROC-tracer library: Runtimes Generic Callback/Activity APIs. The goal of\nthe implementation is to provide a generic independent from specific\nruntime profiler to trace API and asyncronous activity."
        },
        {
            "name": "spdlog",
            "description": "Very fast, header only, C++ logging library"
        }
    ],
    "dependent_to": [
